textDisplay:
Treason. The offense of attempting to overthrow the government of the state to which the offender owes allegiance; or of betraying the state into the hands of a foreign power. Webster.
In England, treason is an offense particularly directed against the person of the sovereign, and consists (1) in compassing or imagining the death of the king or queen, or their eldest son and heir; (2) in violating the king's companion, or the king's eldest daughter unmarried , or the wife of the king's eldest daughter unmarried , or the wife of the king's eldest son and heir ; (3) in levying war against the king in his realm; (4) in adhering to the king's enemies in his realm. giving to them aid and comfort in his realm, giving to them aid and comfort in the realm or elsewhere; and (5) slaying the chancellor, treasurer, or the king's justices of the one bench or the other, justices in eyre, or justices of assize, and all other justices assigned to hear and determine, being in their places doing their offices. 4 Steph. Comm. 185-193; 4 B1. Comm. 76-84.
" Treason against the United States shall consist only in levying war against them, or in adhering to their enemies, giving them aid and comfort." U. S Const. art.3,& 3, cl. 1.

textDisplay:
Unlike Nixon, Trump will drag down the Republican Party several national election cycles. Nobody should be blamed for this more than the Republican Senators who still support him.
Nonetheless, an opportunity has presented itself for these senators to salvage their party — and also be on the right side of history. They can do this by not getting in the way of the release to the Jan. 6 Committee of Trump’s activity calendars and handwritten notes. These subpoenaed items — in and of themselves — are enough to show Trump’s extensive involvement in the insurrection — even expose him criminally.
Standing in the way of the Commission obtaining these items will undermine its work and will keep the Republicans on the wrong side of history. It will also deprive them of the last opportunity to salvage their Party. Yes, rebirth comes from the ashes — just like Nietzsche says.
